    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You could do it like that:</p>\n<pre><code>File folder = new File(&quot;your/path&quot;);\nFile[] listOfFiles = folder.listFiles();\nif(listOfFiles != null) {\n for (int i = 0; i &lt; listOfFiles.length; i++) {\n  if (listOfFiles[i].isFile()) {\n    System.out.println(&quot;File &quot; + listOfFiles[i].getName());\n  } else if (listOfFiles[i].isDirectory()) {\n    System.out.println(&quot;Directory &quot; + listOfFiles[i].getName());\n  }\n }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Do you want to only get JPEG files or all files?</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 735316,
      "reputation" : 2338,
      "user_id" : 692054,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a2728f91bcbe3460f0e15fe4ef263dfe?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
